---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Department of Inquiry — Classified Briefing"
  description="You weren't supposed to find this. But here you are."
  theme="scifi"
  accent="#00b4d8"
  accentGlow="rgba(0, 180, 216, 0.4)"
>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="doi-briefing">
      <p class="doi-stamp">// CLASSIFIED — CLEARANCE LEVEL: CURIOUS //</p>
      <h1 class="doi-title">Department of Inquiry<br /><span>Operative Onboarding File</span></h1>

      <div class="doi-body">
        <p>
          Well. You found it. Either someone tipped you off, or you're exactly the kind of person
          we've been looking for.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Department of Inquiry doesn't advertise. We don't post on job boards. We don't
          hand out business cards at Federation galas. We find our people the old-fashioned way —
          they find <em>us</em>.
        </p>
        <p>
          You've demonstrated initiative, technical curiosity, and a healthy disregard for staying
          in the lanes you're told to stay in. That's not a liability. That's a <strong>qualification</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          Jax Jensen didn't fill out an application either.
        </p>

        <hr class="doi-divider" />

        <p class="doi-label">// FIELD NOTE FROM HANDLER //</p>
        <p>
          The Federation spans a hundred worlds. Most people spend their entire lives on one.
          The ones who dig — the ones who pull threads and follow breadcrumbs through server logs
          and response headers and places they weren't supposed to look — those are the ones
          who change things.
        </p>
        <p>
          Stay curious. Read the books. The answers are in there too.
        </p>
        <p class="doi-sign">
          — M.P. Tayle<br />
          <span>Handler, Unofficial Division</span>
        </p>

        <hr class="doi-divider" />

        <p class="doi-label">// BONUS INTEL //</p>
        <p>
          One more thing the thorough among you may appreciate: <a href="/humans.txt">/humans.txt</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <a href="/" class="doi-back">← Return to cover identity</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .doi-briefing {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 4rem auto;
    padding: 2.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 0 40px rgba(0, 180, 216, 0.1), inset 0 0 60px rgba(0, 180, 216, 0.03);
    font-family: 'Rajdhani', sans-serif;
  }

  .doi-stamp {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .doi-title {
    font-family: 'Orbitron', monospace;
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 4vw, 2rem);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .doi-title span {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.55em;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
  }

  .doi-body p {
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .doi-body a {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .doi-divider {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .doi-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem !important;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem !important;
  }

  .doi-sign {
    color: var(--color-text-muted) !important;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .doi-sign span {
    font-size: 0.85em;
    font-style: normal;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .doi-back {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .doi-back:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
